      <bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
         <head>Biography</head>
         <p>
            <persname>James M. Hill</persname> (<date>1809-1889</date>) owned a store in <geogname>North Madison, Connecticut</geogname>.  He was also a constable.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>The <persname>James M. Hill</persname> Papers consist primarily of the business records of his store in <geogname>North Madison, Connecticut</geogname>.  The records include account books and  business ledgers. Nine account books cover the period 1832-1842, one business ledger tracks accounts by names of customers, and a second lists alcoholic beverages sold. The papers also contain an account book for the schooner "Baltic," a mathematics workbook, bills and receipts, legal papers documenting Hill's work as a constable, and miscellaneous papers including tax and donation lists.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a" id="a4">
         <head>Organization</head>
         <p>
            <emph render="bold">Series I: Store Financial Records</emph> (<date>1832-1844</date>) include account books and business ledgers. Nine account books cover the period 1832-42, one business ledger tracks accounts by names of customers, and a second lists alcoholic beverages sold.</p>
         <p>
            <emph render="bold">Series II: Financial Records</emph> (<date>undated, 1831-1886</date>) contains an account book for the schooner "Baltic," and various bills and receipts.</p>
         <p>
            <emph render="bold">Series III: Personal and Legal Papers</emph> (<date>undated, 1836-1888</date>) contains a mathematics workbook, legal papers documenting Hill's work as a constable, and other papers including tax and donation lists.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
         <head>Related Material</head>
         <p>Archives &#x0026; Special Collections has a substantial collection of materials pertaining to Connecticut history and business records, see especially the <extref href="http://www.lib.uconn.edu/online/research/speclib/ASC/findaids/Account/MSS19790001.html">Account Books Collection</extref>.  For detailed information on these collections please contact the <extref href="http://www.lib.uconn.edu/online/research/speclib/ASC/collections/curatorinfo.cfm?curatorid=4">curator</extref> or ask at the reference desk.</p>

